 form of   Fleming  .","Americanized form of Flemish <b>Vleminckx</b>: patronymic from <b>Vleminck</b>, an ethnic name for someone from Flanders, Middle Dutch <i>vleminc</i>."]},{"name":"Flanders","meanings":["English: ethnic name from Middle English <i>Fla(u)ndres</i> ‘Flanders’, denoting someone from Flanders, a historical region covering parts of modern-day Belgium, France, and the Netherlands. Compare   Fleming  ."]},{"name":"Fleeman","meanings":["English: variant of   Fleming  ."]},{"name":"Flemming","meanings":["German: ethnic name for someone from Flanders, Middle High German <i>vlaeminc</i>. People from Flanders spread throughout Germany, as well as England, in the Middle Ages as clothmakers and dyers.","English: variant of   Fleming  ."]},{"name":"Flamenco","meanings":["Spanish: ethnic name from <i>flamenco</i> ‘Fleming, Flemish person’ (see   Fleming  )."]}]},{"name":"Reyner","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["from earlier <i>Reinher</i>, composed of <i>ragin</i> ‘advice’ + <i>heri</i> ‘army’."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Reyner Fleming III was born about 1219, in Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom as the son of John Fleming I. He had at least 3 sons with Rosamund Horbury. He died about 1274, in his hometown, at the age of 57."},"et":{"Abt 1219–Abt 1274":"umbes 1219–umbes 1274","1219–1274":"1219–1274","1226–1276":"1226–1276","1242–Male":"1242–Surnud","1244–Male":"1244–Surnud","1250–1307":"1250–1307","1180–1251":"1180–1251","1242":"1242","1274":"1274","1251":"1251","1250":"1250","Abt 1219":"umbes 1219","1180":"1180","Abt 1274":"umbes 1274","Bef 1251":"enne 1251","Abt 1250":"umbes 1250","1226":"1226","1244":"1244","1276":"1276","1307":"1307","1219":"1219","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Wath upon Dearne, Yorkshire, England":"Wath upon Dearne, Yorkshire, England"},"fi":{"Abt 1219–Abt 1274":"noin 1219–noin 1274","1219–1274":"1219–1274","1226–